article.headline: Longwood 85, Gardner-Webb 84
article.story: FARMVILLE, Va. -- Ryan Bogan hit a free throw with five seconds remaining in the game to lift Longwood to an 85-84 victory over Gardner-Webb on Tuesday night. Bogan was fouled by Grayson Flittner four seconds after Gardner-Webb's Aaron Linn tied the score at 84. Dana Smith scored 18 points to lead five Longwood (2-1) players in double figures. Kevin Swecker added 14 points, followed by E.J. Dawson, Martiz Washington and Bogan with 11 points each. Anton Silver led Gardner-Webb with 21 points and nine rebounds. Linn finished with 20 points, Flittner had 18 and Joshua Henley added 16 points for the Bulldogs. Longwood took a 48-32 halftime lead, but Gardner-Webb opened the second half on a 17-6 run to cut the lead to 54-49 with 15:18 remaining. The Bulldogs finally tied the game at 84 on Linn's jumper with nine seconds remaining.
